# Yggdrasil — AI Context

> Read this file at the start of every conversation or task. It is the map; the other docs are the territory.

---

## What Is Yggdrasil

Yggdrasil is an AI-augmented architecture knowledge-graph platform that keeps a living, queryable model of a software system synchronized with its codebase via CI/CD. The system is queried through a web GUI, a REST API, and an MCP interface usable from any AI client (Cursor, Claude Desktop, custom scripts).

**Three distributable artifacts per release:**
- Backend container (ECR → Elastic Beanstalk)
- MCP facade container (GHCR, public — `docker run … ghcr.io/yggdrasil/yggdrasil-mcp:latest`)
- Ratatosk CLI (PyPI — `pip install ratatosk`)

**Full offline/desktop mode**: `docker-compose + Ollama`, zero cloud credentials required.

---

## Architecture Quick Reference

**Pattern**: Modular Django monolith — single project, each bounded context is a Django app.

```
src/yggdrasil/
├── auth/        # Session auth, personal access tokens (SHA-256 hashed), RBAC
├── graph/       # Element, Relationship, Stereotype, Package, Diagram
├── changeset/   # ChangeSet, ChangeSetItem — ALL writes go through here
├── munin/       # Agentic planner (larger LLM) — reads ChangeSets, produces graph ops
├── ratatosk/    # RataskRun model, CLI integration models, run history
├── mcp/         # FastMCP server — exposes full service layer as MCP tools
├── api/         # DRF routers + serializers — REST interface for GUI, CLI, MCP
├── llm/         # LLMClient protocol + AnthropicClient / OpenAIClient / OllamaClient
└── web/         # Django views, HTMX partials, templates, Cytoscape.js rendering
```

**Dependency rules (no circular imports):**
```
munin    → graph, changeset, llm
ratatosk → graph, munin, llm
mcp      → graph, changeset, munin (via api service layer)
api      → graph, changeset, munin, ratatosk, auth
web      → api (via service layer), graph, changeset
```

**Key design decisions:**
1. All writes (human, Ratatosk, MCP) go through the Munin / ChangeSet pipeline — graph integrity never bypassed
2. `LLMClient` protocol abstracts Anthropic / OpenAI / Ollama — swap per environment
3. Celery + Redis for async tasks (local docker-compose, no SQS)
4. Server-rendered HTMX — testable with Django test client, no browser required for most tests
5. Blue/green EB CNAME swap for zero-downtime production releases

**Full architecture**: `docs/architecture/SAO.md`

