## How to Build Features (BPE Summary)

1. Read the feature spec in `docs/features/act-*/` (Gherkin)
2. Promote executable scenarios to `features/at/` or `features/e2e/` during BPE-04/05 (keep in sync with docs)
3. Read `docs/architecture/SAO.md` for the relevant bounded context
4. Check `docs/ux/2_dialogue-maps/screen-flow.md` for Screen IDs and navigation
5. Skeleton first: docstrings + type hints + stubs
6. Write failing tests (red)
7. Implement minimum code to pass (green)
8. Refactor; all tests green
9. PR with conventional commit message

