## Running Locally

```bash
# One-time setup
make provision          # installs deps, copies .env, installs pre-commit hooks

# Start backing services (Postgres + Redis)
make up                 # or: make up-desktop (adds Ollama for local LLM)

# First run
make migrate            # apply migrations
make run                # http://localhost:8000  (or F5 in Cursor)

# Tests (no Docker required)
make test               # unit + integration, in-memory SQLite
make test-at            # acceptance tests (behave-django)
make check              # lint + typecheck

# Useful shortcuts
make shell              # Django shell_plus
make seed               # load fixtures/seed.json
```

**F5 in Cursor** → launches `Django: Run Server` configuration (`.vscode/launch.json`).
Requires: `.env` present + `make up` running (Postgres + Redis).
